A 23-year-old man accused of causing £20,000 of damage to the Houses of Parliament during an eight-hour stand-off on the roof has appeared in court today. 

Braydon Liam Anderson, 23, allegedly smashed a stain glass window, broke an ornamental crown and a CCTV camera and pulled valuable brickwork and masonry off the historic landmark. 

It sparked a major security alert on Saturday night with police, fire engines and specialist negotiators scrambled to the scene. 

