Anderson became visibly distressed when he was told he would be remanded in custody for the night.

He shouted out: 'It's my right to protest' as he was led away to the cells.

Anderson, of Portland Place, Northampton, is accused of trespass on a protected site and criminal damage.

He has not yet entered any pleas. 

